So I came from Atlanta to visit and it was suggested to come here from other hospitality review companies. Nonetheless, due to the 11pm curfew concierge warned us about; we decided to call to make a reservation as suggested. Upon calling at 9pm we were told by the host over the phone, no reservations were taken but we could walk in “it was empty”. The website validated this information as did their social media - “no reservations taken”. We show up and end up standing on line for 30+ minutes which was fine, but when we got to the door - Thomas was at the door and asked our party count. There was three of us. We continued to stand for 20+ minutes awaiting a table patiently until a party of three asked us if they could squeeze by. Apparently, they knew the other host that gladly let them in alongside Thomas with no questions asked or regard for those at the door. After a additional 15 minutes of waiting, my friend asked Thomas how long was the wait, he quoted us an additional 25 minutes. At that point we made mention we saw him let people in that staff was familiar with, he stated “they made a reservation” I then let him know we called a hour before and was told “no reservations were accepted” he told us “they made it yesterday”. After Thomas walked away we grabbed a random host and asked him what was the reservation policy in which he stated reservations were not accepted.  It is now 11:18 and we were escorted onto the top floor in which was empty - sat and handled instantly.  Me being in the industry I think it’s terrible to let people wait over a hour as you barade regulars past them as their dollars matter more.  Since sitting, service has been well. I will not return though and do not recommend. We weren’t drunk, we came to shoot footage regarding the hospitality sector. It starts at the door and the disrespect was disgusting.

Service and Staff was good. However the Manager of the Restaurant doesn't seem to understand how Reservations work. We had a Reservation for 7:30pm and waited outside (in a separate line for people who had reserved), until 8:30pm. This by itself would probably already be the worst case of overbooking I have witnessed at a Restaurant, but the mis-management doesn't stop there. Mambo's also kept a separate line for people who didn't reserve, and let those people in at the same pace as the people who reserved. So instead of waiting 30 min because they let too many people reserve for 7:30, you now wait 1 hour. The solution is quite simple, don't do Reservations if you don't understand how they work. Or if you do Reservations, and people are waiting outside 1 hour past their Reservation time, don't let walk-ins sit down in their place. Then again this a tourist trap on Bourbon Street so they probably don't care about customers returning. The food itself was ok, they deep fry all their seafood in a thick batter, likely to cover up for a lack of quality in ingredients. So many better places to eat in the same price range in NOLA, and they won't make you wait 60 min past your reservation time.

Mambo's was a welcome bit of comfort in a stress-filled time for myself and the world. My 35 weeks pregnant girlfriend and I were on a mission to find a suitable establishment to get something delicious for lunch in the French Quarter. My girlfriend, in her advanced stage of pregnancy, would only be able to walk a very short distance and it was important that we not go too far from our hotel. We were dismayed to find so many of our options had been eliminated before our search began by the ever inconveniencing Covid.  We had nearly given up when we strolled up on Mambo's.  The lady at the door was welcoming and when she saw my girlfriend struggling to find her mask in her purse, she told her not to bother and offered her one that the restaurant had ready. We were invited to the 3rd floor and were seated.  The server introduced herself and with a very friendly and accommodating attitude. She recommended the specials which sounded wonderful although we ultimately ordered off of the menu instead. We had the redfish prepared two different ways which we exchanged samples of. Both dishes proved to be top of the line and made the lunch quite enjoyable. I finished my grilled redfish as well as the two side which were a delicious cup of cheese grits and a cup of greens that was superb.  My girlfriend completed her sides and asked for a box to bring home her blackened Mango's redfish topped with a crawfish sauce. The bill was a bit more than I was hoping to spend but the food and service were certainly worth the extra expense. I look forward to exploring more of the menu in the future.
